promise of senior leader deng xiaoping that after years of 
enforced egalitarianism it was permissible for some people to get 
rich before others 
soon teachers and office workers began discovering that barely 
literate snack vendors pulled in more money than they many young 
businessmen bought motorcycles a few could even afford cars 
