<DOCNO> AP890803-0164 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
three new moons were discovered around 
neptune by cameras on the voyager 2 space probe as it hurtled 
toward the blue planet jet propulsion laboratory scientists said 
thursday 
the discoveries bring the number of known neptune moons to six 
including longknown triton and nereid and a moon found earlier 
this summer by voyager 
voyager 2 was 22 million miles from neptune when the moons were 
confirmed by scientists wednesday indicating there may be many 
more discoveries as the space probe draws closer in the next few 
weeks 
finding the moons may presage discovery of narrow rings around 
neptune similar to those around saturn that is because the moons 
are orbiting in a region where rings are thought to exist said 
richart terrile one of the team of scientists studying images 
transmitted by voyager 
the whole ring arc idea has it that satellites will be in 
association with the rings and the fact were seeing the moons 
already is encouraging richard terrile using a term for partial 
rings 
the new moons were temporarily named 1989 n2 1989 n3 and 1989 
n4 the objects were spotted in images from voyagers tv cameras 
and tracked for five days they were confirmed as moons when they 
followed predicted orbits 
the trio appear to range between 60 miles and 125 miles in 
diameter and are in circular equatorial orbits moving in the same 
direction as neptunes rotation triton for unknown reasons 
orbits in the opposite direction 
voyager 2 was launched in 1977 and has explored jupiter saturn 
and uranus now 27 billion miles from earth it is heading at more 
than 42000 mph on a course to pass within 3000 miles of neptune 
on aug 24 
the number of discoveries at such a great distance from neptune 
suggests more finds are likely according to terrile 38 a 10year 
voyager project veteran who is among two dozen members of the 
imaging team 
at this time in the last encounter uranus we had only found 
one moon i think the fact that we found four now bodes well for 
finding more he said 
the moons may shed light on how neptune formed neptune has a 
large atmosphere and little is known about what its core is made of 
and what is going on in there 
moons can provide a sample of material from a planet or be 
material captured by it terrile said 
a planet just normally doesnt form by itself it leaves 
behind debris he said adding that the debris can be in the form 
of moons or rings 
study of moons can also tell scientists about such events as 
heating collisions and geological activity in the solar system 
the moons have on them since they are surfaces an imprinted 
history of whats gone on terrile said 
for the moment the discoveries raise more questions than 
answers if there is a ring system is it regular or irregular 
we know very little about whats there yet were plunging a 
spacecraft right through the system terrile said 
scientists believe voyager 2 is in a fairly safe position he 
said but if there is an irregular system we might find that its 
a rather hazardous place to fly the spacecraft through 
the newfound moons were only points of light on the images but 
the resolution will improve about 5 percent each of the next 10 
days and then improve by 10 percent a day terrile said 
of the three 1989 n3 is closest to neptune orbiting 17000 
miles above the planets clouds and completing one orbit every 8 
hours and 10 minutes 
orbiting 23300 miles above the clouds 1989 n4 circles neptune 
in 10 hours and 20 minutes 1989 n2 is 30000 miles above the 
clouds and completes each orbit in 13 hours and 30 minutes 
voyager 2 spotted the first new moon 1989 n1 on june 21 and 
tracked it until confirmation in july 
 
</TEXT>
