<TEXT>
the six defendants convicted of racketeering in 
the landmark princetonnewport securities fraud case must forfeit a 
total of 38 million significantly less than what the government 
wanted a jury ruled 
federal prosecutors had asked that the defendants relinquish 
salaries and other interests of more than 21 million 
the largest forfeiture amount decided wednesday 3 million was 
against james sutton regan a former partner in princetonnewport 
partners lp a defunct securities house 
his partnership interest was placed at 133 million and his 
salary at 175 million 
four other defendants were each ordered to forfeit 200000 
they are former drexel burnham lambert inc trader bruce lee 
