following forfeiture from the other defendants zarzecki 11 
million partnership interest and 267483 in salary rabinowitz 
791191 partnership interest and 454507 in salary berkman 
762613 partnership interest and 558328 in salary and smotrich 
124583 in salary 
the case involved a series of prearranged stock transactions 
between 1984 and 1986 the government alleged that the defendants 
illegally bought and sold stocks to generate phony tax losses 
the case overlapped the governments 98count fraud and 
racketeering indictment of former drexel junkbond chief michael 
milken much of the same evidence is expected to be introduced at 
milkens trial scheduled to begin in march 1990 
princetonnewport based in princeton nj and newport beach 
calif went out of business after the indictment was brought last 
august defense lawyers said at the time that the charges alone 
though unproven destroyed the firms ability to do business 
