the nations major retailers thursday posted minor to moderate 
july sales gains with some chains benefiting from further good 
results in womens apparel 
but the sales growth at store chains around the country partly 
reflected improvements from weak business last summer and didnt 
imply that a rebound in consumer spending has begun retail 
industry analysts said 
although july is normally a slow time for shopping analysts 
keep track of monthly sales figures from department stores mass 
merchandisers and discounters for clues about consumer behavior 
consumer spending supplies about twothirds of the power for total 
economic activity 
a relatively poor performance by industry leader sears roebuck 
and co illustrated the consequences of the sluggish pace of 
consumer spending sears tiny sales increase of 04 percent held 
down the industrys average 
an index compiled by investment firm drexel burnham lambert inc 
showed sales at 40 general merchandise chains apparel and 
furniture retailers rose 46 percent in july following junes 47 
percent rise 
