overall results were adversely affected by softness in sales of 
durable goods which are expensive items such as ovens or 
dishwashers that consumers typically refrain from buying when they 
feel financially pinched 
consumers have reacted to rising mortgage payments and other 
credit costs lately by curtailing shopping trips or postponing 
purchases of items usually financed with loans until interest rates 
recede 
