<TEXT>
italian grain merchant ferruzzi finanziaria spa 
said thursday it had dropped a moot lawsuit challenging a chicago 
board of trade order apparently aimed at preventing ferruzzi from 
cornering the us soybean market 
the board of trade termed the move a victory but ferruzzi said 
its withdrawal of the us district court lawsuit was a technical 
matter only and that it still planned to sue the exchange for 
losses incurred when it was forced to sell more than 20 million 
bushels worth of soybean futures contracts 
ferruzzi has denied trying to corner the market 
the withdrawn lawsuit filed in chicago sought an injunction 
overturning the board of trades july 11 order requiring all 
traders to reduce their holdings in the july soybean futures 
contract to 1 million bushels by july 20 
judge james zagel denied the injunction request on july 13 and 
the july soybean contract expired on july 20 rendering the suit 
moot 
ferruzzi said it dropped the lawsuit tuesday noting the suit 
applied to an act governing a period that now was over 
we continue to prepare a lawsuit that will seek compensation 
for the damages ferruzzi suffered as a result of the order the 
milanbased company said 
nevertheless the board of trade said it welcomed the suit 
withdrawal which demonstrates the integrity of futures market 
selfregulation at the board of trade 
ferruzzi has said that before the board of trades liquidation 
order it held contracts to take delivery of 23 million bushels of 
soybeans in july 
board of trade officials said only about 12 million bushels of 
soybeans were available for delivery against those contracts 
the exchange said it issued the order which did not mention 
ferruzzi to prevent defaults on contracts to deliver soybeans and 
to ensure the orderly expiration of the july contract 
ferruzzi one of the worlds largest soybean processers has 
denied trying to corner the market saying it needed all the 
soybeans it had contracted to buy in order to keep its plants 
running and to meet the demand for its products 
