dollar if the dollar continues to fall it could limit the federal 
reserves willingness to lower interest rates for fear of weakening 
the dollar even more said hugh a johnson a senior vice president 
at first albany corp 
in the secondary market for treasury bonds prices of shortterm 
governments were down between 332 point and 316 point 
intermediate maturities fell point to 732 point and longterm 
issues were point to 1116 point lower the telerate inc 
financialinformation service reported 
the movement of a point equals a change of 10 in the price of a 
bond with a 1000 face value 
