<TEXT>
shareholders of hanson plc at a meeting in london 
thursday approved the british conglomerates 35 billion pound or 
57 billion offer for the mining giant consolidated gold fields 
plc hanson said 
approval was expressed in an overwhelming show of hands among 
those present shareholders voting by proxy also were 
overwhelmingly in favor of the offer said hanson britains 
fourthlargest company 
on june 22 hanson in a move that took the stock market by 
surprise offered 31 billion pounds then worth 48 billion for 
consolidated gold fields 
consolidated gold fields accepted hansons bid in early july 
under the agreement hanson said it would offer 1430 pounds or 
the equivalent of 2345 a share for consolidated and give 
consolidated shareholders warrants to purchase new hanson shares 
also under the agreement consolidated agreed to pay 
shareholders the equivalent of a 65cent dividend for the fiscal 
year ended june 30 the warrant and dividend together increased the 
value of hansons offer to 2509 a share 
consolidated has interests in south african gold and platinum 
and us construction materials 
hanson has interests ranging from bricks and everready batteries 
to light industry 
in april a us court blocked a merger bid for consolidated 
from south africancontrolled minorco sa an investment group 
minorcos bid was valued at 365 billion pounds then worth 62 
billion 
a majority of consolidated shareholders indicated that they 
wanted to accept minorcos bid but the us court refused to lift 
an injunction against a minorco takeover arising from an antitrust 
suit 
